FBIS4-27898 "dreas108_c_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-108 Daily Report 4 Jun 1994 North Korea U.S., ROK Stage Air Strike Exercises 1, 2 Jun U.S., ROK Stage Air Strike Exercises 1, 2 Jun SK0406045294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0440 GMT 4 Jun 94 SK0406045294 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, June 4 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists mobilized nuclear-capable F-16 and F-15 fighter-bombers, pursuit-assault planes, VTOL [vertical takeoff and landing] assault planes, electronic jamming planes and early warning planes based overseas and warplanes of the U.S. Airforce stationed in South Korea and the South Korean puppet Airforce, some 500 in all, in surprise air strike exercises against the North in the skies above Yongwol, Tanyang, Umsong and Asan Bay of South Korea on June 1 and 2, according to military sources. Meanwhile, the South Korean puppets fired more than 500 large-calibre machinegun and automatic rifle bullets, charging toward the Military Demarcation Line from Paju County on June 1. Formations of helicopter gunboats and transport helicopters staged ground-attack support and airlifting exercises in the skies above Pochon, Yonchon and Chorwon and Inje, South Korean Kangwon Province, on June 2. Facts clearly show how desperately the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean puppets are trying to increase their combat capacity in a war against the North.
